-- FACTBOX: Breakdown of GM's job cut plans for Opel
-- 
-- Wed Nov 25, 2009 1:49pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/11/25/us-gm-jobs-factbox-idUSTRE5AO3YG20091125

 

 RUESSELSHEIM, Germany  (Reuters) - Opel's labor leader Klaus Franz detailed parent company General Motors' plans to cut jobs at the European carmaker. 

 The following is a summary of planned job cuts, with the highest losses per site at the top: * RUESSELSHEIM, Germany - Nearly 2,500 at Opel headquarters to go, of which: - around 1,300 in administration - 862 in production - 548 in engineering and development center.